 X modular two where X is an integer.

6
00:00:13,345 --> 00:00:14,545
 What is X mod two?

7
00:00:14,545 --> 00:00:17,145
 This is the least significant bit of X.

8
00:00:17,145 --> 00:00:19,365
 What does the least significant bit of X tell you?

9
00:00:19,365 --> 00:00:21,540
 It tells you whether X is odd or even.

10
00:00:21,540 --> 00:00:25,695
 In particular, it's one if X is odd and zero if X is even.

11
00:00:25,695 --> 00:00:29,655
 Now, what's another way of looking at this least significant bit of X?

12
00:00:29,655 --> 00:00:31,680
 Well, we can take X divided by two.

13
00:00:31,680 --> 00:00:36,970
 If it's even then the remainder is going to be zero because it's a multiple of two,

14
00:00:36,970 --> 00:00:41,570
 and if it's odd, then the remainder when X divided by two is going to be one.

15
00:00:41,570 --> 00:00:42,810
 So we looked at X mod two.

16
